<br>
If the pack doesn't like what you, I, or anyone else posts, oh frikken well.<br>
<br>
I've made some wildly unpopular posts here. There are people that would rather delete a thread (had they the power to do so) than read my response (qed the thrashing of the Pledge argument between Fkin and myself). There are folks who will jump on my case for just seeing me post an opinion.<br>
<br>
Whatever.<br>
<br>
This is a flame board. Some people cannot understand the difference between a flame and pointless sniping, admittedly, but it is a place where folks come to vent, and they generally do so in a blatantly asinine manner. It is essentially the status quo hereabouts.<br>
<br>
Esmalyn is right, you are primarily getting grief because you are apparently a conservative. Join the club. I'm a fairly blatant Libertarian/Conservative as well, and catch hell for my opinions. Still, if my convictions cannot stand under the fire of the local harpies, they are not worth holding in the first place.<br>
<br>
I will not exhort you to stay as I think that you are perfectly correct in thinking that you don't &quot;fit&quot; here. I will say, however, that you can carve out a place should you desire it. It likely will not be worth the effort if you are not taking some sort of enjoyment from the bantering and bickering as it is though.<br>
<br>
Sorry to see you go... <p>a_Bearhat01<BR>
