&quot;Jynn, it sounds like you're taking up others' causes, entrenching yourself in their shoes. Appreciating how others feel is commendable but you (generic) can go too far.&quot;<br>
<br>
Well, the reason for posting those two examples is so that people would not think that all I notice is &quot;me&quot; and point out that there is a pattern of jumping on really trivial things at times and it's not always trivial things that I do.  I understood the gist of his message, but apparently it was difficult for others.  The reason I didn't thank Barto for the invitation or say goodbye was I was a little weary at that point and didn't feel like opening another battlefront.<br>
<br>
&quot;BTW, I think I read the post here. It should be moved to the general forum. Oh sh*t, I'm being mean again.&quot;<br>
